   Business Brief -- ITT Corp.:
   Insurance Unit Signs Letter
   To Buy Surety Bond Line
</HL>
<DATE>
09/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B13F
</SO>
<CO>
   ITT U.CUA
</CO>
<IN>
INSURANCE (INS)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   ITT Hartford Insurance Group said it signed a letter of
intent to acquire the surety bond business of Commercial
Union Insurance Co. Terms were not disclosed.
   ITT Hartford said the acquisition is expected to increase
its written premiums from surety bonds by about 10%. In 1989,
ITT Hartford wrote about $67 million in such premiums.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   ITT Hartford is a unit of New York-based ITT Corp.
Commercial Union Insurance is a U.S. subsidiary of
London-based Commercial Union PLC.
