<HL>
   Waste Management
   Says Wheelabrator
   Holders Clear Merger
</HL>
<DATE>
09/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B13B
</SO>
<CO>
   WMX WTI WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   OAK BROOK, Ill. -- Waste Management Inc. said Wheelabrator
Technologies Inc.'s shareholders approved a previously
announced merger agreement between the two companies.
   Waste Management said the agreement increases its
ownership of Wheelabrator's common stock to 55% from 22%.
Wheelabrator, a Hampton, N.H., developer and operator of
waste-to-energy facilities, will remain a separate public
company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The waste disposal concern said that in exchange for each
share of Wheelabrator Technologies held, shareholders of
record will receive 0.469 Waste Management share and 0.574
Wheelabrator share. Under the agreement, four Waste
Management officers were named directors of Wheelabrator, in
addition to the eleven current directors. They are Jerry E.
Dempsey, Jerome D. Girsch, James E. Koenig, and Edwin G.
Falkman.
