   Canada's Jobless Rate Rises
</HL>
<DATE>
09/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canada's unemployment rate rose to 8.3% of the
work force in August from 7.8% in July as a result of the
country's current economic slowdown, Statistics Canada, a
federal agency, said. The August figure was the highest
jobless rate since October 1987.
   Employment declined 0.5% in August to 12.6 million, its
lowest level since last December.
