   Chevron Wins Jet Fuel Contract
</HL>
<DATE>
09/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6
</SO>
<CO>
   CHV AN X.PAR ELP WSN SUN GI UTX G.HFA
</CO>
<IN>
PETROLEUM (PET)
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Chevron USA, a unit of Chevron Corp.,
received a $153.9 million Defense Logistics Agency contract
for jet fuel.
   The award was the largest of more than $500 million in jet
fuel contracts announced by the Pentagon.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Other jet fuel contracts went to Phoenix Petroleum Co.,
$76.8 million; Amoco Oil Co., a unit of Amoco Corp., $75.1
million; Barrett Refining Corp., $57.5 million; Hawaiian
Independent Refinery Inc., a unit of Pacific Resources Inc.,
$56.7 million; El Paso Refining Co., $35.9 million; Western
Petroleum Co., a unit of Western Co. of North America, $20.5
million; U.S. Oil &amp; Refining Co. $14.8 million; Sun Refining
&amp; Marketing, a unit of Sun Co., $13.3 million; Giant
Industries Arizona Inc., $11 million, and Gary-Williams
Energy Corp., $10.7 million.
   In addition, the Army awarded United Technologies Corp. a
$77.6 million contract for helicopters. Hoechst Celanese
Corp. got a $27 million Air Force contract for chemical
defense suits.
   ---
