   Student Loan Marketing Association -- $100 million issue
of notes, due Sept. 20, 1993, was priced at par to float
initially at a spread of 100 basis points above the
Treasury's three-month bill. The noncallable notes will float
weekly and pay interest quarterly. The rate on the notes will
be reset each quarter at a spread of 100 basis points above
the three-month Treasury bill, except if the three-month
London Interbank Offered Rate exceeds 9% on any quarterly
payment date.
                                                                                                       

